cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.GT, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper involves computer vision techniques to create a 3D reconstruction of a soccer game, which suggests that it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a 3D viewer and Augmented Reality device, which falls under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. The paper also involves estimating depth maps, which could fall under the graphics (cs.GT) sub-category. The use of a CNN for training and comparison with state-of-the-art techniques suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the mention of interactive rendering suggests that it could also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
